    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Diervilla maximowiczii are anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, antimicrobial, and antiviral. Its anti-inflammatory property is attributed to the presence of flavonoids, which inhibit the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines. Diervilla maximowiczii's antioxidant property is linked to the presence of phenolic acids, which scavenge free radicals and protect against oxidative stress. The antimicrobial property of this plant is due to the presence of terpenoids, which disrupt the cell membranes of microorganisms and inhibit their growth. Its antiviral property is attributed to the presence of saponins, which interfere with viral attachment and penetration into host cells.",
