    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Diervilla maximowiczii are flavonoids and phenolic acids, particularly kaempferol, quercetin, and isorhapontigenin, which have been shown to exhibit anti-inflammatory, antioxidant, and antimicrobial activities. Additionally, the plant contains iridoids such as diervillein and maximowiczin, which have been found to possess anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects. The presence of these bioactive compounds in Diervilla maximowiczii is attributed to its ability to produce sesquiterpenoids, including diervillein and maximowiczin, which are responsible for its medicinal properties. Studies have also identified other constituents like alkaloids and saponins, although their exact roles in the plant's healing properties are still being researched. The overall composition of Diervilla maximowiczii's bioactive compounds supports its traditional use in treating various health conditions, including inflammation and infections.",
