    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Diervilla maximowiczii are derived from its flowers, leaves, and roots, which are used to create various medicinal products. Infusion and decoction are liquid preparations made by steeping the plant material in hot water, used to treat digestive issues and skin problems. Tincture is a concentrated liquid extract prepared by soaking the plant material in a solvent, often used for its antiseptic and anti-inflammatory properties. Diervilla maximowiczii salve is a topical preparation made by infusing the plant material in a carrier oil, used to treat skin irritations and wounds. Diervilla maximowiczii tea is a liquid preparation made by steeping the plant material in hot water, used to treat various health issues, including fever and respiratory problems.",
